### 5. ambiguous read (owner, no account) -> 409 + accounts (never guesses)

GET /api/twitter/jar
{"error":"multiple accounts synced for twitter; pass ?account=<id> or bind the token to one","accounts":["111","222"]}
[HTTP 409]
### 6. account-qualified read ?account=111 -> jar 111

GET /api/twitter/jar?account=111
{"plugin":"twitter","subject":"owner","jar":{"twid":"u%3D111","auth_token":"acct1-token"}}
[HTTP 200]
### 7. account-qualified read ?account=222 -> jar 222 (distinct)

GET /api/twitter/jar?account=222
{"plugin":"twitter","subject":"owner","jar":{"twid":"u%3D222","auth_token":"acct2-token"}}
[HTTP 200]
### 8. mint a token BOUND to account 222 (caps:jar)
{"token":"tok-twitter-772a358bb29b40aebd90afa7","plugin":"twitter","subject":"owner","caps":["jar"],"account":"222"}
### 9. read WITH that token (no ?account) -> resolves jar 222 via token.account
{"plugin":"twitter","subject":"owner","jar":{"twid":"u%3D222","auth_token":"acct2-token"}}
[HTTP 200]
### 10. token bound to 222 does NOT read 111 even if ?account=111 asks (token wins)
{"plugin":"twitter","subject":"owner","jar":{"twid":"u%3D222","auth_token":"acct2-token"}}
[HTTP 200]
